HEADWORD: Confessionalism
<hw>Con*fes"sion*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>An exaggerated estimate of the importance of
giving full assent to any particular formula of the Christian
faith.</def> <rj><au>Shaff.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confessionalist</ent>⟦br⟧
